item.title: PI Help
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Uhm. Drugs.

Yeah, clarify more.
I think you are asking: How can I make my pi server compatible with pegasus’s 317 client loading 474.

And the answer is, load the client and try to login to your server (make sure the ips are correct). If it doesn’t allow you in look on the client/server cmd for errors. if it does, talk to npcs, fight them, and do tasks like that to make sure the bytes are streamed the same.
If it’s all good and there’s no errors then you have to do nothing.
